						               													<description>Content: board, 2 big dice, 35 wooden chips&amp;#10;&amp;#10;This game board is like a kind of flipper, where the players play in their chips, in order to get out some more for themselves.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;At the beginning of the game, a chip is placed on each of the three corner spaces of the game board. All other chips are equally distributed to the players. Eventually leftover chips are put on the last space marked with an arrow.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The players roll a die and set a chip on the corresponding space on the game board, 1 beeing the center space. If there is already one or more chips on the space, the player rolls again and moves the entire stack accordingly.&amp;#10;What a player moves over the arrow field onto the table are his winnings.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;GIN is game No. 10 (of a least 12) in a family called &amp;quot;Miniplays&amp;quot;.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
